originalText.text: Don't park here. They damaged the front of my car, the manager later said he didn't see anyone damage it on the video. The customer service sucks. You call and get voicemail boxes that are not set up yet. I believe this company is shady based upon my experience with this incident. I'm still trying to get my incident resolved. If it gets resolved properly I'll delete this bad review.

originalText.text: BEWARE, unlike any other garage I’ve used in Manhattan for 25 years, it closes at midnight! I said I was coming back for my car at 11:30 or 11:45 PM, would have expected courtesy of them telling me to make sure I was back by midnight because of unusual closing time. Instead, arrived around 12:10 to find gate down and my car was trapped there overnight. I had to waste 4 hours to come back next day and pay an extra $47. Plenty of other options in the area, DO NOT USE!

originalText.text: I park here 2x per week and typically retrieve my car around 8:00 p.m. The daytime staff is polite and friendly.  Unfortunately,  the evening attendant is incredibly rude! If I arrive to get my car earlier due to a schedule change,  I  am told that he cannot get my car because it's buried even if I call to tell him that I will be earlier than expected.  He still yelled at me. If the price wasn't so good I'd park elsewhere.

originalText.text:
1. I’ve parked my car here multiple times out of convenience of it being close to home. Every time I leave it, someone goes through my stuff, I have pictures of before dropping it off and after. I voiced it out and they didn’t touch my things...that one time.

2. We have a snow storm outside, my car is in the garage. I know that for 24 hours we pay $35, the guy just said it’s $45. I asked when the rates go up and he had the audacity to say 2 weeks ago. I just checked on their website to book the space and it says $35. There is literally no number for me to voice this out, I’m really upset they are taking advantage of the snow storm to make more money out of people when their company literally has the prices online. The audacity...
